React Hooks:
It is mainly used to manage state and life cycle features in functional components.
State: it allows components to be dynamic ,interactive and capable of responding to user input or change over time.#hold the values for the compinents
1)useStateHook: allows you to add state to functional components.
Syntax:
Const[state,setState]=useState(intial value)
State:this is current state
setState:this is a function to update the state
intial value:the value you want to set as the intial value.



import { useState } from 'react'

import './App.css'

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0)

  return (
    <>
      
      
      <div className="card">
        <button onClick={() => setCount((count) => count + 1)}>
          count is {count}
        </button>
      </div>
    </>
  )
}

export default App
